<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-13489] camel-undertow: consumer thrown NPE when the body cannot be converted to ByteBuffer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-13489</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Assuming we have a simple route like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
from(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;undertow:http:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//localhost:{{port}}/incompatibleData&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;    .transform().constant(Collections.singletonMap(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;key&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;val&quot;&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This code will cause an NPE on UndertowConsumer because the body cannot be converted to a ByteBuffer &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, instead of an NPE we should use mandatoryConvertTo so the exception is more clear.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/master/components/camel-undertow/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/undertow/UndertowConsumer.java#L156&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/master/components/camel-undertow/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/undertow/UndertowConsumer.java#L156&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
